### Step 10: Leak audit (recommended before any decision)

Run `/backtest <slug> --leak-audit` after a clean run. The auditor mode deliberately injects a small set of canonical look-ahead violations into a sandbox copy of the strategy and verifies the harness either catches them or shows materially better numbers (which is the smoking gun). If the harness misses a violation, fix the harness, not the strategy. Document the audit in the report.

### Step 11: Log the run

Append to `intel.jsonl`:

