## Important Rules

- **Point-in-time data is non-negotiable.** No PIT, no backtest. Refuse to proceed past Step 2 without it.
- **Survivorship correction is non-negotiable.** Acknowledged-bias mode exists only to keep the report honest, not to legitimize unreliable numbers.
- **Realistic costs are non-negotiable.** Commissions + slippage + impact + borrow + financing. Defaults are conservative; user can override but cannot zero them silently.
- **Walk-forward, not in-sample / out-of-sample.** If the user insists on a single train/test split, tag the report `Unreliable`.
- **The honesty section is mandatory.** Every report lists at least one limitation. A report with no limitations is the limitation.
- **No live trading from this skill.** This skill produces a report. Live trading happens through `/paper-trade` and then explicit ship gates.
